ince Per Item shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),(399,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/ModulesHome.html','09.01','Shipping Modules','Shipping Modules\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules\r \r PhreeBooks has a built in Shipping Manager module to aid in the generation of rates and labels for your products. Additional modules may be added to further enhance the number of shipping options. A shipping log is kept with pertinent inforamton to monitor your packages and verify status. \r Standard Shipping Modules\r Federal Express (FedEx) - Includes rates, label generation, tracking, and logging \r United Parcel Service (UPS) - Includes rates, label generation, tracking, and logging \r United States Postal Service (USPS) - rates, logging \r Flat Rate Shipping - rates, logging \r Free Shipping - rates, logging \r Per Item Shipping - rates, logging \r Store Pickup (Will Call) - rates, logging \r Table Rate Based Shipping  - rates, logging \r Zone (State/Province) Based Shipping  - rates, logging \r Related Links\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r Invoice Manger\r Adding new Shipping Modules\r Removing Shipping Modules'),(400,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/storepickup/WillCallHome.html','09.01.05','Shipping Modules - Will Call','Shipping Modules - Will Call\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Will Call\r \r PhreeBooks includes a shipping module to calculate will call shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Will Call Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Will Call row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the Will Call module. \r   Click the Will Call row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Will Call shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),(401,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/freeshipper/FreeHome.html','09.01.03','Shipping Modules - Free Shipping','Shipping Modules - Free Shipping\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Free Shipping\r \r PhreeBooks includes a shipping module to calculate free shipping charges (with handling). \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Freeshipper Shipping Module \r \r       Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Freeshipper row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r       Click on Install to install the Freeshipper module. \r   Click the Freeshipper row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Freeshipper shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),(402,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch09-Shipping/02-Installation/InstallationHome.html','09.02','Shipping Modules - Installation','Shipping Modules - Installation     Shipping Modules - Installation  Additional shipping modules can be downloaded from www.PhreeBooks.com and installed into the /modules/shipping/directory. Please refer to the installation instructions included with each module for details installing the particular module.'),(403,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch10-ImportingExporting/ImpExpHome.html','10','Importing/Exporting','Importing/Exporting     Importing/Exporting PhreeBooks has several ways to import data into the system.  With the exception of beginning balances, import operation are made through the Tools -&gt; Import/Export menu. Beginning balances are imported through the General Ledger -&gt; General Journal Utilities menu.  General Import Procedure     From the Tools -&gt; Import/Export menu, select the tab of the type of import you want to perform.   Scroll down the list and select the template to import from, press the Open icon.    The criteria tab will display the criteria for which to import data. This will allow filtering the imported data to only include the fields you are interested in.   Click on the fields tab. The table displayed lists the fields available to import. Column fields are defined as follows:            Sequence - Indicates the sequence the field appears in the import file format.       Field Name - This is a textual name for identifying the field to import. It is linked to the actual database field name.        Processing - Phreebooks allows for processing the data during the import operation. Imported values can be trimmed, formatted, etc. to meet the criteria of the database value ranges.        Import - Specifies whether the field is available for import. Generally, all fields are importable except the primary index field (usually named id)        Show - Indicates whether the field will be included in the import list or not. Yes = include, No = don\'t include            Arrange the fields to match the sequence of the import data.   Save the import template for future use (it\'s best to try a few trial runs to validate the import template before importing the entire data file.   Press the Options tab and select the delimiter and text qualifier for the import file. Check whether the first row contains header information. The header information is ignored during the import if checked, the import is sequence driven.     Press the Browse button and select the file to import.   Press the Import icon to initiate the import. NOTE: It\'s best to try a smaller file at first on a test system until the import template is validated.  General Export Procedure Data can be exported using the same template as importing. The data file is downloaded to your browser and can be saved or viewed locally. Another option is to use the reportwriter tool to build the export data and select the csv option when creating the report.  Importing Contacts (Vendors/Customers/Employees)  Contacts can be imported into PhreeBooks through csv or tab delimited format. Up to 5 of each billing and shipping addresses may be imported with each contact. Importing Inventory Inventory can be entered into PhreeBooks as a csv or tab separated file. NOTE: make sure all additional inventory fields are set-up in the system before importing inventory. (See Inventory - Tabs and Fields)  Importing Beginning Balances Importing beginning balances is covered in the following section: Installation - Importing Beginning Balances  The following journals can be imported. Inventory, Purchase Orders, Purchase/receive Inventory, Sales Orders, Sales/Invoices. For inventory, the SKU\'s must be present in the system prior to importing values. For the rest, the vendors/customers will be created during the import process, if necessary.  Importing Chart of Accounts &nbsp; Copying Companies  Companies can be copied to a new database along with selected information ranging from tables only to every record stored in the source company. Company operations are found in the Tools -&gt; Company Manager menu.'),(404,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch04-Setup/CharacterSets.html','04.03','Character Sets Setup','Character Sets Setup     Character Sets Setup &nbsp;'),(405,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch04-Setup/MultiCompany.html','04.05','Setting up Multiple Companies','Setting up Multiple Companies        Setting Up Multiple Companies PhreeBooks requires an unique database for each company.  NOTE: Prior to adding or copying a new company, the database must exist in the system. Phreebooks WILL NOT generate the database! Adding a new company     Go to Tools-&gt;Company Manager.   Enter the database name in the Add New Company fieldset.   Enter the company full name in the Add New Company fieldset.   If you want the demo data loaded, check the Add Demo Data box.    Click the Add New Company button.     Note: When a new comany is created, a directory under /my_files is created named the same as the database. Additional directories and  system files are created under this new directory to store uploads, logs and other information pertaining to the newly created company.   Copying a company     Go to Tools-&gt;Company Manager.   Enter the database name in the Copy Company fieldset.   Enter the company full name in the Copy Company fieldset.   Check the boxes for the information you want to transfer over to the new company.    Click the Copy Company button.     Note: When a  company is copied, a directory under /my_files is created named the same as the database. Additional directories and system files are created under this new directory to store uploads, logs and other information pertaining to the newly created company.   Deleting a company    WARNING: THIS IS A NON-RECOVERABLE EVENT! ALL DATA WILL BE LOST! BE SURE TO BACK UP YOU FILES BEFORE DELETING A COMPANY.     Select the company from the pulldown menu in the Delete Company fieldset.   Click the Delete Company button and confirm the deletion.   All company data will be erased. This includes all database tables as well as the directory (and subdirectories) under the /my_files/ directory named after the database.  &nbsp;'),(406,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch04-Setup/CompanySetup.html','04','Company Setup','Company Setup     Company Setup Upon initial setup, the company information is loaded in the database. If additional companies are added, they will appear at login in a pull down menu. The user will need to select the company to use at login. Once selected, the copmpany will remain in use for the duration of the session. Additional companies can be added through the Tools-&gt;Company Manager menu.'),(407,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch04-Setup/LocationsBranches.html','04.04','Setting up Multiple Locations','Setting up Multiple Locations     Setting up Multiple Locations (Branches)  PhreeBooks supports multiple branches/stores. The company information is gathered during setup but branch information is entered through the Setup-&gt;Maintain Branches menu. To enter a new branch:    Select Setup-&gt;Maintain Branches.   The current branches are listed. To edit a branch, select the edit icon for the branch to edit, or, to enter a new branch press the Add button.    Enter a branch ID. Branch ID\'s should not contain spaces or special characters. It is best to use an abbreviation or store number as the Branch ID.   Enter the Branch information requested by the form. Required information is identifed by a * next to the input box.   Press the Save button to save the record.   To delete a branch:    Select Setup-&gt;Maintain Branches.   The current branches are listed. To delete a branch, select the delete icon for the branch to delete.   Confirm the deletion of the record. NOTE: If the branch is used in a journal record, it cannot be deleted. Instaed, check the inactive box and the branch will no be shown on the pull down menus for the order forms.  Related Links &nbsp;'),(408,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch04-Setup/Currencies.html','04.02','Currencies Setup','Currencies Setup     Currencies Setup PhreeBooks supports multiple currencies. The default currency is set  during setup but additional currencies can be entered through the Setup-&gt;Currencies menu. To enter a new currency:    Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.   Enter the fields request in the popup form.    Press the Save button to save the record.   To delete a currency:    Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.   The current currencies are listed. To delete a currency, select the delete icon for the currency to delete.   Confirm the deletion of the record. NOTE: If the default currency is deleted, a new default currency should be selected.  Related Links'),(409,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch04-Setup/Languages.html','04.01','Language Setup','Language Setup     Language Setup Languages are automatically detected at login. However, the default language can be set in the includes/configure.php file to pre-select the language during login.   The login script reviews the directories under the General module to see what language modules have been installed. Each user can select their prefered language and it will remain in effect during the duration of the session. Language modules are available throught eh Phreebooks website, www.PhreeBooks.com.'),(410,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/departments_types.html','15.03.75','Table departments_types','Table departments_types\r \r \r \r Table departments_types\r Table departments_types helps organize employees by grouping into department types. They can be used form reporting to help filter report output.\r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   description\r   varchar(30)\r   NOT NULL \r   Textual description of the department type.'),(411,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/departments.html','15.03.70','Table departments','Table departments\r \r \r \r Table departments\r Table departments holds a list of departments used to help organize the employee list. They can be grouped by fields derived in the departments_type table.\r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r char (15)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Holds unique department ID. \r \r \r   description\r   varchar(30)\r   NOT NULL\r   Textual description of the department. \r \r \r   subdepartment\r   enum (0,1) \r   0\r   Flag indicating if this is a sub-department of another department. Nesting is unlimited. \r \r \r   primary_dept_id\r   char(15)\r   NULL\r   If sub-department flase set, this hold the id of the parent department \r \r \r   department_type\r   tinyint\r   0\r   Holds the department tye as defined in table department_types \r \r \r   department_inactive\r   enum (0,1) \r   0\r   Flag indicating if the department is inactive.'),(412,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/contacts.html','15.03.52','Table contacts','Table contacts\r \r \r \r \r Table contacts\r Table contacts holds information\r regarding all customer, vendor, employee, and branch accounts. It is\r tightly coupled with table address_book. Table contacts holds the\r specific information whereas the addresses are stored in table\r address_book. \r \r This table is updated through the maintain customer (or vendor,\r employee,&nbsp;branch) or added through the order process through the\r add/update checkbox.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r auto_increment\r N/A\r PRIMARY KEY - unique id assigned to each account entry\r \r \r type\r char\r c\r INDEX - Defines the type of entry. Handy to know when building\r reports to specify as a hidden criteria &nbsp;to filter out unwanted\r accounts. Defined types are:c - Customerv - Vendore - Employeeb - Branch\r \r \r short_name\r varchar(20)\r NOT NULL\r INDEX - This field holds a short reference name (called Customer\r ID, Vendor ID, etc.) used to help organize the accounts. Acts as a\r unique identifer in a more user readable fashion than the id field. \r \r \r inactive\r enum (0,1)\r 0\r Flag to mark and account as inactive. Can be used to prevent orders to a account.\r \r \r contact_first\r varchar (32)\r NULL\r Used for employee type accounts to hold the employee first name. \r \r \r contact_middle\r varchar (32)\r NULL\r Used for employee type accounts to hold the employee middle name or initial\r \r contact_lastvarchar (32)NULLUsed for employee type accounts to hold the employee last name store_idvarchar (15)NOT NULL&nbsp;gl_type_accountvarchar (15)NOT NULLHolds\r the general ledger account to use as the default in the order screen.\r When set, this account will appear in the line item account position.gov_id_numbervarchar (16)NOT NULLHolds the employee id number, tax resale number of the accountdept_rep_idvarchar (16)NOT NULLHolds\r the department rep id assigned to this account. When entered, the rep\r name will be inserted into the &nbsp;sales rep entry field of the order\r screen.account_numbervarchar (16)NOT NULLHolds\r an assigned customer or vendor account number. Useful on sales orders\r and purchase orders to identify your companies account number with your\r customer or supplier.special_termsvarchar(32)0PhreeBooks\r allows individual payment terms by account. A value of 0 indicates that\r the default terms should be used. The value is encoded and can be\r changed in the Maintain Customer/Vendor screen.first_datedate0000-00-00Set the first time the account is created. Useful to know how long the account has been active.last_updatedateNULLIndicates the last time the account was updated. Useful to know when the last time the account was accessed.last_date_1dateNULLlast_date_2dateNULL'),(413,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/tax_authorities.html','15.03.170','Table tax_authorities','Table tax_authorities\r \r \r \r Table tax_authorities\r Table tax_authorities holds regulative authorities and the tax rate applied to transactions. They are used in association with table tax_rates to determine the tax rate applied to sales/purchases. This table applies the tax to the appropriate accounts and tax_rates determines which authority receives the tax. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r tax_auth_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   description_short\r   char(15)\r   NULL\r   Short description used for reports and where display space is limited \r \r \r   description_long\r   varchar(64)\r   NULL\r   More detailed description used where all the details of the tax authority is required. \r \r \r   account_id\r   varchar(15)\r   NULL\r   General Ledger account associated with this tax authority. This field determines where the tax value calculated in a transaction is placed. \r \r \r   vendor_id\r   int(11)\r   0\r   Account (Contact) associated with this tax_authority. \r \r \r   tax_rate\r   float\r   0\r   Tax rate value'),(414,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory_special_prices.html','15.03.125','Table inventory_special_prices','Table inventory_special_prices\r \r \r \r Table inventory_special_prices\r Table inventory_special_prices is used to override the price sheets on a sku by sku, proce sheet by price sheet level. Price sheets are defined to help create multi-level pricing accross the entire inventory dtabase. If certain sku-s require a different fomula, special price are used. For example, you may have defined two price sheets, retail and dealer, that set your default price levels. However, one of your sku\'s requires a different pricinf formula. Special prices allows an individual sku to have it\'s own formula for the sku and for ach price sheet. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   inventory_id\r   int(11)\r   0\r   This is the record number in the inventory table that this special price applies to. Basically the sku. \r \r \r   price_sheet_id\r   int(11)\r   0\r   This is the record id of the price sheet that this special price applies to. \r \r \r   price_levels\r   varchar(255)\r   NULL\r   This is the encoded price level/value applied to the sku.'),(415,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/tax_rates.html','15.03.175','Table tax_rates','Table tax_rates\r \r \r \r Table tax_rates\r Table tax_rates holds regulative tax rates for sales and purchase transactions. They are used in association with table tax_authorities to determine the tax rate applied to sales/purchases. This table determines the tax to apply to the transaction  and tax_authorities determines how the tax is distributed to the authorities. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r tax_rate_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   description_short\r   varchar(15)\r   NULL\r   Short name used in reports and where description space is limited. \r \r \r   description_long\r   varchar(64)\r   NULL\r   Longer mre detailed description of the tax rate, may include what taxz authorities are involved. \r \r \r   rate_accounts\r   varchar(64)\r   NULL\r   encoded string containing the GL accounts and rate values. \r \r \r   freight_taxable\r   0, 1 \r   0\r   Determines whether freight is taxable or not'),(416,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/configuration.html','15.03.45','Table configuration','Table configuration\r \r \r \r Table configuration\r Table configuration holds constants used throughout PhreeBooks. They\r are grouped by the field configuration_group_id with table\r configuration_group to separate the constants into user defined\r groupings. Some group id\'s are hidden to the user as they are used by\r add-on modules for shipping, payments, etc. \r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r configuration_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto-increment number for record id.\r \r \r \r configuration_titletextNOT NULLThe title used in the Company -&gt; {category} listing as seen by the user. configuration_keyvarchar (255)NOT NULLUNIQUE\r - This field defines a constant load with every page and used through\r most of the scripts. The syntax is all uppercase with underscores to\r separate words.configuration_valuetextNOT NULLThe value assigned to the constantconfiguration_descriptiontextNOT NULLThe description used to help the user set the value of the constant. configuration_group_idint (11)0INDEX - Maps to the configuration_group table to help organize the configuration constants.sort_orderint (5)Defines the order for which the configuration item appears in the listing by group.last_modifieddatetimeNULLDate the record was last modified.date_addeddatetime0000-00-00 00:00:00Date the configuration constant was added to the table.use_functiontextDefines the function to use when displaying the configuration constant.set_functiontextDefines\r the function to use to format the input field of the configuration\r value. This can be to restrict the choices (pull-down menu) or map\r textual descriptions to sytem values.'),(417,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/reconciliation.html','15.03.150','Table reconciliation','Table reconciliation\r \r \r \r Table reconciliation\r Table reconciliation hold the list of cleared receipts/payments with the bank or other institution. One or more cash accounts can be reconciled with the bank statement. The table will contain one record for each period/GL account combination. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   period\r   int(11)\r   0\r   Accountig period \r \r \r   gl_account\r   varchar(16)\r   NULL\r   General Ledger account\r \r \r   statement_balance\r   float\r   0\r   Balance in the account after the period/gl_account has been reconciled. This amount will usually be zero after reconciliation but may not be zero if reconciliation is in process. This allows for partial reconciliations, saving the intermediate results.\r \r \r   cleared_items\r   text\r   \'\'\r   Encoded list of items selected to be cleared in a given period/gl_account.'),(418,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/chart_of_accounts_types.html','15.03.40','Table chart_of_accounts_types','Table chart_of_accounts_types\r \r \r \r Table chart_of_accounts_types\r Table chart_of_accounts_types holds the general ledger accounts types\r and identifies how the accounts map to the accounting standards. The\r type should not be changed but the descriptions may be for language\r translations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \r NOTE: DO NOT EDIT THE id OR asset FIELD. These vales are used by the system to validate the balance sheet and income statement. \r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Identifies the account type id number.\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r descriptionvarchar (30)NOT NULLNarrative description of the account type. Can be chaged for language translations.assetenum (0, 1)0States whether the account type is an asset or liability. DO NOT EDIT THIS FIELD.'),(419,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/accounts_notes.html','15.03.18','Table accounts_notes','Table accounts_notes\r \r \r \r Table accounts_notes\r Table accounts_notes is linked to table accounts and holds open text information pertaining to a particular account. The id fields links directly to the id fields of table_accounts.\r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r auto_increment\r N/A\r PRIMARY KEY - unique id assigned to each account entry\r \r \r   notes\r   text\r   &nbsp;\r   Holds the notes for accounts of all types (customers, vendors, employees, branches)'),(420,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory_categories.html','15.03.95','Table inventory_categories','Table inventory_categories\r \r \r \r Table inventory_categories\r Table inventory_categories  defines extra categories whic help organize inventory attributes. Categories appear as tabs in the maintain inventory screen. \r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r category_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   category_name\r   varchar (32) \r   NOT NULL\r   Holds the name of the inventory category. The category appears as a tab in the maintain inventory script. \r \r \r   sort_order\r   int (2) \r   0\r   Sort order to organize the tabs. Will appear after the defaults tabs (system, bom, master stock) \r \r \r   category_description\r   varchar (80)\r   NOT NULL\r   Textual description of the category. Mostly used in reports.'),(421,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/chart_of_accounts.html','15.03.30','Table chart_of_accounts','Table chart_of_accounts\r \r Table chart_of_accounts\r Table chart_of_accounts holds the general ledger cost accounts used for\r every transaction in PhreeBooks. The&nbsp;table is created and\r loaded during install and can be altered in the General Ledger\r -&gt; Chart of Accounts menu. \r \r NOTE: A general ledger account cannot be deleted if there is a journal\r entry posted against the account.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r char (15)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Identifies the chart of account number\r (or value).\r \r descriptionvarchar (64)NOT NULLProvides a texual description of the account. Set by the user and used for reports.subaccountenum (0, 1)0Flag to indicate if this account is a subaccount of another accountprimary_acct_idchar(15)NULLIf the subaccount is set, this field holds the account that is the master account.account_typeint (4)0INDEX - Specifies the type of account. See chart of accoutn types for a description of allowed account types.next_refchar (15)NOT NULLThis field is not used at this time.account_inactiveenum (0, 1)0Specifies if the account is active or inactive.'),(422,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory_history.html','15.03.115','Table inventory_history','Table inventory_history\r \r \r \r Table inventory_history\r Table inventory_history holds the historical record of inventory as items as they are received and sold. Only items that are considered cost-trackable are stoed in this table. These include, stock-items, item assemblies, Serialized items, Master stock items. This table is the primary source of costing when calculating the cost of goods sold for tracking gross profit the the income statement. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   ref_id\r   int(11)\r   0\r   This links the received item to the journal record where the item was received.\r \r \r   sku\r   varchar(15)\r   NULL\r   The inventory item SKU \r \r \r   serialize_number\r   varchar(24)\r   NULL\r   If the item is a serialized item, the serial number is stored here. NOTE: For serialized items, only one item may be received/sold per line on the order form.\r \r \r   remaining\r   float\r   0\r   The number of units of the item remaining. This value will initially start out as the number received and will be reduced as items are sold.The value should never be less than zero. \r \r \r   unit_cost\r   float\r   0\r   The cost the the item when it was purchased. This value is used when calculating the cost of good sold. \r \r \r   post_date\r   datetime\r   NULL\r   The date the inventory item was received \r \r \r \r &nbsp;'),(423,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory_fields.html','15.03.110','Table inventory_fields','Table inventory_fields\r \r \r \r Table inventory_fields\r Table inventory_fields allows the user to add additional attributes to their inventory items. Inventory fields are organized alphabetically through inventory categories. \r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r inv_field_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   entry_type\r   varchar (20)\r   NOT NULL\r   Identifes the type of field to enter, text, html, drop-down, checkbox, etc. \r \r \r   field_name\r   varchar (32) \r   NOT NULL\r   Identifies the fields name as it appears in the table inventory \r \r \r   description\r   varchar (64) \r   NOT NULL\r   Textual description of the field\r \r \r   category_id\r   int (11) \r   0\r   Identifies the id of the category for sorting when editing the inventory item. \r \r \r   params\r   text\r   &nbsp;\r   Encoded data depends on the tpye of field being entered. NOTE: Do not edit this entry.'),(424,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/audit_log.html','15.03.25','Table audit_log','Table audit_log\r \r Table audit_log\r Table audit_log keeps a historical trail of the actions performed in\r PhreeBooks. All major events are tracked from logging in,&nbsp;order\r posting, inentory item editing, etc.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r auto_increment\r N/A\r PRIMARY KEY - unique id assigned to each log entry\r \r action_datetimestampTimestamp of the audit log entryuser_idint (11)0Specifies the user id of the action. Links to the table \'users\'.reference_idvarchar (32)NULLINDEXactionvarchar (64)NULLspecifies the action added to the log. Content varies depending on what functions was performed.amountfloat0Specifies\r the amount of the transaction. Will be 0 if the action did not involve\r an amount, i.e. logging in, updating an inventory item, etc.'),(425,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/zones.html','15.03.190','Table zones','Table inventory_history\r \r \r \r Table zones\r Table zones holds the state/province information for each country type. The table can be updated through  Setup -&gt; Zones.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   countries_iso_code_3\r   char(3)\r   NULL\r   Holds the ISO code of the country where the zone is located. \r \r \r   zone_code\r   varchar(32)\r   NULL\r   Holds the abreviation o the zone (e.g. NY for new York) \r \r \r   zone_name\r   varchar(32)\r   NULL\r   Holds the full name of the zone.\r \r \r \r &nbsp;'),(426,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/DBTablesHome.html','15.03','Database Reference','Database Reference     Database Reference &nbsp;'),(427,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/import_export.html','15.03.80','Table import_export','Table import_export\r \r \r \r Table import_export\r Table import_export hold the definitions and parameters to import or export data to PhreeBooks. In general, only data can be added to one table at a time. The exeptions are accounts (vendors, customers, employees) where shipping and billing addresses may also be imported. To import beginning balances, use the import beginning balances scripts as these scripts populate many tables and post the transaction properly to the journal.\r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   group_id\r   char (3)\r   NOT NULL\r   Hold the group the the import_export definition is a part of. Current defined groups are:\r       inv : Inventory\r       ap: Accounts Payable\r       ar : Accounts Receivable\r       hr: Employees (Human Resources)\r   \r     \r \r \r   custom\r   enum (0,1) \r   1\r   Flag to indicate is this is a standard import/export definition or has been saved and customized for a particular purpose. \r \r \r   security\r   varchar (10) \r   NOT NULL\r   Not used at this time \r \r \r   title\r   varchar (32)\r   NOT NULL\r   Textual title of the import/export definition. Appears in the description tabs at the Import/Export main page. \r \r \r   description\r   varchar (255)\r   NOT NULL\r   Textual descriptio to help identify what the purpose of the import/export definition is. \r \r \r   table_name\r   varchar (32) \r   NOT NULL\r   Specifies the default table name without prefix to bas the import/export definition from.\r \r \r   primary_key\r   varchar (32) \r   NOT NULL\r   Specifies the primary key from the table_name (above) to use as an index to retrieve data. \r \r \r   params\r   text\r   &nbsp;\r   Encoded field holds user specific parameters. NOTE: This field should not be edited in the database table. \r \r \r   criteria\r   text\r   &nbsp;\r   Encoded field holds user specific criteria. Fields include user defined criteria of which there may be more than one. NOTE: This field should not be edited in the database table.\r \r \r   options\r   text\r   &nbsp;\r   Encoded field holds user specific options. Fields such as export format, fielnames, etc. NOTE: This field should not be edited in the database table.'),(428,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/reports.html','15.03.155','Table reports','Table reports\r \r \r \r Table reports\r Table reports holds the  table, page and display details for the reports/forms displayed in PhreeBooks.  A single report will contain one field in table reports and several in report_fields. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   description\r   varchar(30)\r   &nbsp;\r   This is a brief description of the report. It is used as the report title for reports and is the default filename if the report is exported or imported. \r \r \r   narrative\r   varchar(255)\r   &nbsp;\r   This is a textual description used to provide details of the report or form. Information such as language, page setup, paper size, report purpose may be part of this field. \r \r \r   reporttype\r   char(3)\r   &nbsp;\r   Two possible types are frm (form) and rpt (report). \r \r \r   groupname\r   varchar(9)\r   &nbsp;\r   Indicates the group the report or form is a part of. Group names are defined in the reportwriter language file. Reports contain a single code to indicate the type whereas forms contain a two string code to indicate the type and usage. For reports and forms, the first value determines which tab the report appears in and for forms, the second code determines which folder in the tab the form appears in.\r \r \r   standard_report\r   0, 1 \r   &nbsp;\r   Indicates if the report is a standard report or has been customized by a user. Standard reports can only be customized through the report builder tool whereas custom reports can be saved by users after special cusotmization to meet his or her needs through the report display script.\r \r \r   special_report\r   varchar(32)\r   &nbsp;\r   REPORTS ONLY. When a report can not be generated with the standard reportwriter structure, a special report may be used to generated the fields displayed in the reports. A special class must be declared here (field contains the class name) to be included and executed to help reportwriter pull the correct information. The Balance Sheet and Income Statement report are examples of reports that require the special_report field. \r \r \r   table1\r   varchar(25)\r   &nbsp;\r   The first database table used to pull information. REQUIRED\r \r \r   table2\r   varchar(25)\r   &nbsp;\r   The second database table used to pull infomraiton. OPTIONAL but if present, must be accompanied with a criteria linking the tow tables.\r \r \r   table2criteria\r   varchar(75)\r   &nbsp;\r   Criteria used to link table1 to table2. OPTIONAL\r \r \r   table3\r   varchar(25)\r   &nbsp;\r   The third database table. OPTIONAL\r \r \r   table3criteria\r   varchar(75)\r   &nbsp;\r   Link to either the first or   second  database table. OPTIONAL\r \r \r   table4\r   varchar(25)\r   &nbsp;\r   The fourth database table. OPTIONAL\r \r \r   table4criteria\r   varchar(75)\r   &nbsp;\r   Link to either the first, second or  third  database table. OPTIONAL\r \r \r   table5\r   varchar(25)\r   &nbsp;\r   The fifth database table. OPTIONAL\r \r \r   table5criteria\r   varchar(75)\r   &nbsp;\r   Link to either the first, second, third or fourth database table. OPTIONAL\r \r \r   table6\r   varchar(25)\r   &nbsp;\r   The sixth database table. OPTIONAL\r \r \r   table6criteria\r   varchar(75)\r   &nbsp;\r   Link to either the first, second, third, fourth or  fifth database table. OPTIONAL'),(429,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory_cogs_usage.html','15.03.105','Table inventory_cogs_usage','Table inventory_cogs_usage\r \r \r \r Table inventory_cogs_usage\r Table inventory_cogs_usage  links the inventory purchase inventory_history table with the journal_main table to account for cogs calculations. The table basically indicates how many of what sku  from what purchase went to what order. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r category_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   journal_main_id\r   int (11)\r   NOT NULL \r   Refers to the id in table journal_main for a transaction \r \r \r   qty\r   float\r   0\r   Qty of the sku used from the history table \r \r \r   inventory_history_id\r   int (11) \r   NOT NULL \r   Refers to the history id of when the item was placed into stock.'),(430,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/users.html','15.03.180','Table users','Table users\r \r \r \r Table users\r Table users holds the login information for the users of PhreeBooks. User accounts can be linked to employee accounts.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r admin_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   admin_name\r   varchar(32)\r   NULL\r   The login name of the user. Must be unique \r \r \r   display_name\r   varchar(32)\r   NULL\r   The name to display in welcome screens\r \r \r   admin_email\r   varchar(96)\r   NULL\r   user email address \r \r \r   admin_pass\r   varchar(40)\r   NULL\r   user password \r \r \r   account_id\r   int(11)\r   0\r   This field links the user account to the employee (Contact) account.\r \r \r   admin_prefs\r   text\r   NULL\r   &nbsp;\r \r \r   admin_security\r   text\r   NULL\r   This field holds the encoded security information for the user defining what modules are accessble and which are not. \r \r \r \r &nbsp;'),(431,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/price_sheets.html','15.03.140','Table price_sheets','Table inventory_history\r \r \r \r Table price_sheets\r Table price_sheets holds the default inventory pricing formulas used for setting prices. Zero or more price sheets may be entered as needed for customers or quantities. Revisoin levels are included to allow for setting effective dates for pricing revisions. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   sheet_name\r   varchar(32)\r   NOT NULL\r   Short name of the price sheet \r \r \r   inactive\r   0, 1 \r   0\r   Status of the price sheet \r \r \r   revision\r   float\r   0\r   Revision level \r \r \r   effective_date\r   date\r   0000-00-00\r   Effective date of the price sheet \r \r \r   expiration_date\r   date\r   NULL\r   Expiration date, when the price sheet is inactive (usually so a new one can take its place) \r \r \r   default_sheet\r   0, 1 \r   0, 1 \r   Specifies the default sheet used for pricing \r \r \r   default_levels\r   varchar(255)\r   NOT NULL \r   Encoded price sheet formula for determining price levels'),(432,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory_ms_list.html','15.03.120','Table inventory_ms_list','Table inventory_ms_list\r \r \r \r Table inventory_ms_list\r Table inventory_ms_list holds the reference information of the sub-items created off of a Master Stock item. Any number of up to two attributes can be used to create a master stock item. For example, color and size would be two attributes with any number of colors and any number of sizes. The number of items created will be attr1 count * attr2 count. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   sku\r   varchar(15)\r   NULL\r   Holds the sku of the created master stock item. This will be the Master Stock base sku (10 characters) plus the 2 character codes for each of the two attributes assigned to the master stock item. \r \r \r   attr_name_0\r   varchar(16)\r   NULL\r   Holds the short description of the first attribute \r \r \r   attr_name_1\r   varchar(16)\r   NULL\r   Holds the short description of the second attribute \r \r \r   attr_0\r   varchar(255)\r   NULL\r   Hold a textual description of the first attribute providing a more detailed description of the attribute.\r \r \r   attr_1\r   varchar(255)\r   NULL\r   Hold a textual description of the second attribute providing a more detailed description of the attribute.'),(433,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory_cogs_owed.html','15.03.100','Table inventory_cogs_owed','Table inventory_cogs_owed\r \r \r \r Table inventory_cogs_owed\r Table inventory_cogs_owed is used to hold sku\'s that sold but are not in inventory to calculate the cost of good sold. Only inventory items that have their costs tracked are placed in this table. When inventory is received in, this table is reviewed to see if any of the received items require a cogs calculation. IF so, the any entries taht use this sku are re-queued for re-post so the cogs can be calculated. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r category_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   journal_main_id\r   int (11) \r   0\r   Refers to the id in table journal_main for a transaction \r \r \r   sku\r   varchar (15) \r   NOT NULL \r   The sku that was not in stock for a sales transaction \r \r \r   qty\r   float\r   0\r   Qty of the sku owed calculation of cost of goods sold \r \r \r   post_date\r   date\r   0000-00-00\r   The post date of the transaction. This value is used for sorting when determining the cost method (FIFO, LIFO, average) to sequence properly'),(434,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory.html','15.03.85','Table inventory','Table inventory\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Table inventory\r The inventory table holds the items available for use PhreeBooks. The definitions are for the base inventory fields as shipped with PhreeBooks. The inventory manager allows additional fields to be added that are not defined within this help file. Refer to the section on Inventory Manager Overview for a detailed explanation of adding additional fields to this table. \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Type\r     Size (value) \r     Comment\r   \r   \r     id\r     integer\r     11\r     auto-increment field used to uniquely identify each inventory item.\r       Primary Key: YES\r       Indexed: YES\r       Unique: YES\r     \r     \r   \r   \r     sku\r     varchar\r     15\r     The unique sku or ID associated with a given inventory item. \r   \r   \r     inactive\r     enum\r     0, 1\r     Specifies if the inventory item is anactive item (true) or inactive (false) \r   \r   \r     inventory_type\r     char\r     2\r     Specifies the type of inventory item. Each type has different properties. The types are defined as follows:\r     SI - Stock Item\r       MS - Master Stock Item\r       NS - Non-stock item\r       DO - Description Only\r       SV - Service\r       LB - Labor\r       AS - Assembly\r       AI - Activity Item\r       CI - Charge Item\r       SR - Serialized\r     \r   \r   \r     description_short\r     varchar\r     32\r     Contains a short description of the inventory item for use primarily in the sales (customer) activities. \r   \r   \r     description_purchase\r     varchar\r     255\r     Contains the vendor description used promarily in the purchases (vendor) activities. This may include vendor part numbers, descriptions unique to the vendor that is ot to be visible to the customer, etc. \r   \r   \r     account_sales_income\r     varchar\r     15\r     Contains the default GL account used for sales (invoicing). This account only applies to the following inventory_type(s): All but Service (SV) \r   \r   \r     account_inventory_wage\r     varchar\r     15\r     Contains the default GL account used for inventory/wage valuation. As items are received, the items value is added to this account. Used for inventoray valuation activities. This account only applies to the following inventory_type(s): SI, MS, NS, SV, LB, and AS. \r   \r   \r     account_cost_of_sales\r     varchar\r     15\r     Contains the default GL account used for calculation of cost of sales. As items are sold, the items value is added to this account. Used for inventoray valuation activities. This account only applies to the following inventory_type(s): SI, MS, NS, SV, LB, and AS. \r   \r   \r     cost_method\r     char\r     1\r     Contais the cost method used for inventory_type(s): SI, MS, and AS. The valid values are (f) - FIFO; first-in first-out, (l) LIFO; last-in last-out, and (a) Average.\r   \r   \r     item_taxable\r     enum\r     0,1\r     Contains a boolean value used for tax calculations on whether the item is taxable or not. A value of 0 will not include the inventory item cost in the tax calculation. \r   \r   \r     item_cost\r     float\r     \r     Contains the cost of the item from the last purchase. This field is set by Zenbooks and cannot be changed by the user. \r   \r   \r     full_price\r     float\r     \r     Specifies the base unit price before adjustment with the price manager.\r   \r   \r     item_weight\r     float\r     \r     Specifies the item weight in the units specified in the configuration options, lb (pounds) or kg (kilograms) are the current choices. \r   \r   \r     quantity_on_hand\r     float\r     \r     Specifies the current quantity on hand. This value will change for purchase/receive inventory, inventory adjustments and sales/invoices activities. \r   \r   \r     minimum_stock_level\r     float\r     \r     User specified minimum stock level used by the system to flag low stock warnings. \r   \r   \r     reorder_quantity\r     float\r     \r     User specified re-order quantity used to help the purchase order process. \r   \r   \r     serialize\r     enum\r     0,1\r     Specifies if the inventory item is a serialized item. Serialized items can only be received as a single unit per line on POs and SOs as the serial number is assigned to the specific line item in question. \r   \r   \r     creation_date\r     datetime\r     \r     Timestamp generated by the system during the initial entry of the item. \r   \r   \r     last_update\r     datetime\r     \r     Timestamp generated by the system the last time a user change was made. \r   \r   \r     last_journal_date\r     datetime\r     \r     Timestamp generated by the system to specify the last time a journal entry ws posted against the inventory item. \r   \r \r Notes:\r &nbsp;\r &nbsp;'),(435,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/journal_item.html','15.03.130','Table journal_item','Table journal_item\r \r \r \r \r Table journal_item\r The general journal table holds the journal entries for every transaction in PhreeBooks. The general journal is broken into two tables, main and item. The main table contains the overview settings that are common for every transaction. The item table contains each individual journal entry and is a many to one relationship with journal_main. \r The table field definitions for the journal_main table are as follows: \r TABLE: journal_item\r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Type\r     Size (value) \r     Comment\r   \r   \r     id\r     integer\r     11\r     auto-increment field used to uniquely identify each journal entry.\r         Primary Key: YES\r         Indexed: YES\r         Unique: YES \r   \r   \r     ref_id\r     integer\r     11\r     Links to the table journal_main id field. this field will be the same for every entry associated with a journal entry, i.e. purchase order, invoice.\r   \r   \r     gl_type\r     char\r     3\r     Specifies the journal item entry type. Entries are coded with the gl_type to track the journal entry. gl_type definitions are as follows:\r       General:\r         ttl - Total entry amount\r         frt - Shipping/Freight charges\r         tax - Sales/VAT Tax entries\r       \r       Payables:\r       poo - purchase order line item ordered\r       por - purchase order line item received\r       pod - purchase order line item expected delivery date\r       pop - purchase/receive item paid\r     Receivables:\r       soo - sales order line item ordered\r       sor - sales order line item shipped\r       sod - sales order line item delivered date\r       sos - sales/invoice item payment received \r     Inventory:\r       -\r     \r   \r   \r     sku\r     varchar\r     15\r     Inventory SKU number.\r   \r   \r     qty\r     float\r     \r     Quantity of items asociated with this journal entry \r   \r   \r     description\r     varchar\r     255\r     Item description \r   \r   \r     debit_amount\r     float\r     \r     The monetary amount for debit transactions.\r   \r   \r     credit_amount\r     float\r     \r     The monetary amount for credit transactions.\r   \r   \r     gl_account\r     varchar\r     15\r     The general leder account associated with this transaction. \r   \r   \r     serialize\r     boolean\r     0,1\r     Flag used for serialized items. \r   \r   \r     serialize_number\r     varchar\r     24\r     Item serial number (valid if serialize is set to 1) \r   \r   \r     post_date\r     datetime\r     \r     Date and time the journal item was posted.\r   \r \r Notes:\r &nbsp;'),(436,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/current_status.html','15.03.65','Table current_status','Table current_status\r \r \r \r Table current_status\r Table current_status holds the next available reference number for various PhreeBooks activities. PhreeBooks will not allow duplicate numbers in the journal for any of these numbers. Fields that are type varchar can use alphanumeric values.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto-increment number for record id.\r \r \r   next_po_num\r   int (11)\r   0\r   Holds the next vendor purchase order number.\r \r \r   next_so_num\r   varchar (16)\r   NOT NULL\r   Holds the next customer sales order number.\r \r \r   next)inv_num\r   int (11)\r   0\r   Holds the next customer invoice  number.\r \r \r   next_check_num\r   int (11)\r   0\r   Holds the next vendor payment number.\r \r \r   next_deposit_num\r   varchar (16)\r   NOT NULL\r   Holds the next customer receipt deposit number.\r \r \r   next_shipment_num\r   int (11)\r   0\r   Holds the next shipment reference number.\r \r \r   next_cm_num\r   varchar (16)\r   NOT NULL\r   Holds the next customer credit memo number.\r \r \r   next_ap_quote_num\r   varchar (16)\r   NOT NULL\r   Holds the next vendor quote number.\r \r \r   next_ar_quote_num\r   varchar (16)\r   NOT NULL\r   Holds the next customer quote number.'),(437,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/journal_main.html','15.03.135','Table journal_main','Table journal_main\r \r \r \r \r \r Table journal_main\r The general journal table holds the journal entries for every transaction in PhreeBooks. The general journal is broken into two tables, main and item. The main table contains the overview settings that are common for every transaction. The item table contains each individual journal entry and is a many to one relationship with journal_main. \r The table field definitions for the journal_main table are as follows: \r TABLE: journal_main\r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Type\r     Size (value) \r     Comment\r   \r   \r     id\r     integer\r     11\r     auto-increment field used to uniquely identify each journal entry.\r         Primary Key: YES\r         Indexed: YES\r         Unique: YES \r   \r   \r     period\r     integer\r     2\r     Accounting period for this journal entry. \r   \r   \r     journal_id\r     int\r     2\r     Code to identify what journal the entry is posted against. Valid codes are:\r         02 - General Journal \r         04 - Purchase Order Journal \r         06 - Purchase Journal \r         07 - Vendor Credit Memo Journal \r         08 - Payroll Journal \r         10 - Sales Order Journal \r         12 - Sales Journal \r         13 - Custoerm Credit Memo Journal\r         \r         14 - Inventory Assembly Journal \r         16 - Inventory Adjustment Journal \r         18 - Cash Receipts Journal \r         19 - Point of Sale Journal \r         20 - Cash Distribution Journal\r         21 - Point of Purchase Journal \r       22 - Shipping Journal\r       \r   \r   \r     post_date\r     date\r     \r     Journal post date \r   \r   \r     store_id\r     varchar\r     15\r     Store id reference for this journal entry \r   \r   \r     description\r     varchar\r     32\r     System defined description for the journal entry (for readability purposes). The journal_id field is used by the system to track entry types.\r   \r   \r     closed\r     boolean\r     0,1\r     When set to 1, indicates that the journal entry has been closed. this flag will remain 0 throughout the transaction until all phases are complete. For example, with a purchase order, the transaction will remain open until all of the items have been received. Item entries for the transaction will occur over time to track actions associated with the journal entry. Once all activities have been completed, the journal entry will close.\r     \r   \r   \r     freight\r     float\r     \r     Holds the total freight cost of the journal entry. \r   \r   \r     shipper_code\r     varchar\r     16\r     Encoded shipping carrier and method. Values are separated by a colon (:). The first value represents the carrier as defined by the installed shipping modules. The second value is the service level. Service levels are defined as (US origin):\r        1DEam =&gt; 1 Day Early a.m.\r 1Dam =&gt; 1 Day a.m.\r 1Dpm =&gt; 1 Day p.m.\r 2Dam =&gt; 2 Day a.m.\r 2Dpm =&gt; 2 Day p.m.\r 3Dpm =&gt; 3 Day\r GND =&gt; Ground\r I2DEam =&gt; Worldwide Early Express\r I2Dam =&gt; Worldwide Express\r I3D =&gt; Worldwide Expedited\r IGND =&gt; Ground (Canada)\r     Shipping service levels definitions can be found in the language file under the shipping module directory (/modules/shipping/language/en_us/language.php). \r     \r   \r   \r     terms\r     varchar(32)\r     NULL\r     This field holds the encoded terms used to post the transaction. \r   \r   \r     sales_tax\r     float\r     \r     The total sales tax for the transaction. \r   \r   \r     tax_auths\r     varchar\r     16\r     Contains the encoded tax authorities assigned to the journal entry. Values refer to the id of the tax authority or authorities in the tax_authorities table separated by colons (:).\r   \r   \r     total_amount\r     float\r     \r     The total amount of the transaction. \r   \r   \r     currencies_code\r     char(3)\r     USD*\r     Sets the currency code used to post the entry. Note that all amounts are in the default currency. This code is used to re-generate the order based on the posted value, currency code and currency value \r   \r   \r     currencies_value\r     double\r     1.0\r     This holds the exchange rate used when the record was posted. If the record was posted in the default currency, this value will be 1.0. If another currency was used to post the transaction, this record will hold the exchange rate used at the time of post.\r   \r   \r     so_po_ref_id\r     int(11)\r     0\r     This field holds the journal record id if the refering entry to this posted record. \r   \r   \r     purchase_invoice_id\r     varchar\r     16\r      Holds the purchase order number, sales order number, invoice number, etc. for applicable transactions. \r   \r   \r     purch_order_id\r     varchar\r     16\r     Holds the reference order number, Customer PO for invoices, for example. \r   \r   \r     recur_id\r     int(11)\r     0\r     For recurring transactions, this holds the id assigned to this and all recurring transactions. If changes are made to a recurring transaction, this id is used to retrieve all related transactions for re-posting. \r   \r   \r     admin_id\r     int(11)\r     0\r     Holds the user ID for the transaction \r   \r   \r     rep_id\r     int(11)\r     0\r      Holds the record number of the employee posting this entry. Settable in the order form. \r   \r   \r     waiting\r     0, 1 \r     0\r     Determines if the journal entry is waiting for more information. This is primarily used for receiving inventory when the invoice has not arrived yet. The inventory receipt can be posted without the invoice number and re-posted later when the invoice arrives.\r   \r   \r     gl_acct_id\r     varchar(15)\r     \r     The general ledger account id. This is ostly a reference as a single journal post will use serveral gl accounts stored in table journal_item with the broken down transaction information. \r   \r   \r     bill_acct_id\r     int(11)\r     \r     Holds the id account (contact) of the billing address used to post the entry.\r   \r   \r     bill_address_id\r     int(11)\r     \r     Holds the id of the address book record for the billing address. \r   \r   \r     bill_primary_name\r     varchar\r     32\r     Holds the remit to address information for payables, sold to information for receivables.\r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     varchar\r     32\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     bill_address1\r     varchar\r     32\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     varchar\r     32\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     bill_city_town\r     varchar\r     24\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     bill_state_province\r     varchar\r     24\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     varchar\r     24\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     bill_country_code\r     char\r     3\r     Formatted with the ISO 3 character codes , i.e. USA, ESP, AUS, etc. \r   \r   \r     ship_acct_id\r     int(11)\r     \r     Holds the id account (contact) of the shipping address used to post the entry.\r   \r   \r     ship_address_id\r     int(11)\r     \r     Holds the id of the address book record for the shipping address. \r   \r   \r     ship_primary_name\r     varchar\r     32\r     Holds ship to information for all transactions. \r   \r   \r     ship_contact\r     varchar\r     32\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     ship_address1\r     varchar\r     32\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     ship_address2\r     varchar\r     32\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     ship_city_town\r     varchar\r     24\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     ship_state_province\r     varchar\r     24\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     ship_postal_code\r     varchar\r     24\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     ship_country_code\r     char\r     3\r     Formatted with the ISO 3 character codes , i.e. USA, ESP, AUS, etc. \r   \r   \r     terminal_date\r     date\r     \r     Date used as follows:\r         Payables: \r         Purchase Orders: Holds the expiration date.\r         Receive Inventory: \r         Receivables:\r         Sales Orders:\r         Invoices: \r   \r   \r     drop_ship\r     boolean\r     0, 1\r     Drop ship flag indicator \r   \r \r Notes:'),(438,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/configuration_group.html','15.03.50','Table configuration_group','Table configuration_group\r \r \r \r Table configuration_group\r Table configuration_group holds the groupings for the configuration\r values. These groupings appear in the Company -&gt; {group} menus. The\r values 0 and 99 are reserved. The value 6 is reserved for the user\r loaded modules such as shipping, payment, etc.\r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r configuration_group_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto-increment number for record id.\r \r configuration_group_titlevarchar (64)NOT NULLTextual title of the group used in generating the pull down menu.configuration_group_descriptionvarchar (255)NOT NULLTextual description of the group.sort_orderint (5)NULLSort order of the groupvisibleint (1)1INDEX - Specifies whether the group is visible in the Company -&gt; {module} menu'),(439,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/shipping_log.html','15.03.165','Table shipping_log','Table shipping_log\r \r \r \r Table shipping_log\r Table shipping_log holds the information regarding item shipped. Most of this information is used by shipping manager to track, and monitor shipments. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   shipment_id\r   int(11)\r   0\r   Holds the id assigned to a given shipment. \r \r \r   ref_id\r   int(11)\r   0\r   Holds the reference for this shipment. Links to purchase_invoice_id field in table journal_main. \r \r \r   reconciled\r   0, 1 \r   0\r   Indicates whether the shipment has been reconciled with the freight bill from the shipping company.\r \r \r   carrier\r   varchar(16)\r   NULL\r   This is the carrier code as setup in the services/shipping/modules/ directory. \r \r \r   method\r   varchar(8)\r   NULL\r   This is the coded method. All modules use the same coding scheme to indicate the method the item was shipped. \r \r \r   ship_date\r   date\r   0000-00-00\r   The date the item was shipped. \r \r \r   deliver_date\r   date\r   0000-00-00\r   The date the item is expected to arrive. \r \r \r   actual_date\r   date\r   0000-00-00\r   The date the item actually arrived. \r \r \r   tracking_id\r   varchar(32)\r   NULL\r   The carreir tracking/bill of lading number. \r \r \r   cost\r   float\r   0\r   The actual cost of the shipment. \r \r \r   notes\r   varchar(255)\r   NULL\r   Any notes associated with the shipment.'),(440,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/accounts_history.html','15.03.15','Table accounts_history','Table accounts_history\r \r \r \r Table accounts_history\r Table accounts_history contains the&nbsp; historical transactions for\r customers and vendors. Data from this table is useful for reports\r showing accout history, totals, and frequency.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r auto_increment\r N/A\r PRIMARY KEY - unique id assigned to each account entry\r \r \r ref_id\r int(11)\r 0\r Referenced the record id of the journal entry, table journal_main.\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r acct_idint(11)0INDEX - Referenced to the account id in the accounts table, table accounts. amountreal double0Total amount of the transaction.journal_idint(11)0Lists the journal ID of the transaction. Refer to the section on the type of journals formore information.purchase_invoice_idchar(16)NULLList\r the PhreeBooks transaction reference. Will be the field Invoice Number\r for sales and purchases, PO Number/SO Number for purchase and sales\r orders.so_po_ref_idint(11)NULLFor sales and purchases, this field wil contain the reference SO/PO record number from the journal_main table.post_datedateNULLLists\r the date and time of the Post Date of the transaction. Not the actual\r date and time of when the record was posted but the Post Date field in\r the orders screen.&nbsp;'),(441,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/currencies.html','15.03.60','Table currencies','Table currencies\r \r \r \r Table currencies\r Table currencies hold the display format for numbers in PhreeBooks. Currency exchange rate values are also saved in this table relative to the default currency. \r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r currencies_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto-increment number for record id.\r \r \r   title\r   varchar\r   &nbsp;\r   Textual description of the currency \r \r \r   code\r   char\r   &nbsp;\r   ISO currency code \r \r \r   symbol_left\r   varchar\r   &nbsp;\r   A single character that is appended to a value left of the number\r \r \r   symbol_right\r   varchar\r   &nbsp;\r   A single character that is appended to a value right of the number\r \r \r   decimal_point\r   char\r   &nbsp;\r   Character to use to separate whole numbers from the fractional part \r \r \r   thousands_point\r   char\r   &nbsp;\r   Character to use to separate three digit groups \r \r \r   decimal_places\r   char\r   &nbsp;\r   Number of number characters to round following the decimal point character \r \r \r   value\r   float\r   &nbsp;\r   Stores the conversion value from the default currency. This value needs to be manually updated through the Setup -&gt; Currencies screen\r \r \r   last_updated\r   datetime\r   &nbsp;\r   Time stamp of the last time the record was updated'),(442,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/project_version.html','15.03.145','Table project_version','Table project_version\r \r \r \r Table project_version\r Table project_version hold the database release information. This data is compared every time a user logs into PhreeBooks the the project release. If the database release is lower, a script is executed to update the database to the same level as the project.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r project_version_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   project_version_key\r   varchar(40)\r   &nbsp;\r   Module/Project name \r \r \r   project_version_major\r   varchar(20)\r   &nbsp;\r   Major release number \r \r \r   project_version_minor\r   varchar(20)\r   &nbsp;\r   Minor release number \r \r \r   project_version_comment\r   varchar(250)\r   &nbsp;\r   Release Comments \r \r \r   project_version_date_applied\r   datetime\r   &nbsp;\r   Timestamp of the record insert/change'),(443,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/report_fields.html','15.03.160','Table report_fields','Table report_fields\r \r \r \r Table report_fields\r Table report_fields holds the field details for the reports/forms displayed in PhreeBooks. The fields are coded by entrytype to inidicate the type of entry it is. A single report will contain one field in table reports and several in report_fields. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   reportid\r   int(5)\r   0\r   Link to the report ID this field is a part of.\r \r \r   entrytype\r   varchar(15)\r   NOT NULL\r   Defines the tpye of field. Types include:\r     datafield: Hold the data field information used in reports and forms. One or moer entries are required per report/form. \r       critfield: Holds the critereia used to filter reports and forms. Zero or more entries are permitted. \r       datefield: Holds the possible date portion of the criteria. Only one entry is permitted per report/form. \r       sortfield: Associated with the sort portion of criteria. Zero or more are permitted. \r \r \r   seqnum\r   seqnum(3)\r   0\r   The sequence number of the field. Used for ordering the fields. This value determines the display order in preparation of the output for reports but is only used to display the order of the fields in Reportbuilder for forms since fields are placed individually on a form. \r \r \r   fieldname\r   fieldname(255)\r   NOT NULL\r   The name of the field as related to the databases used to generate the report/form. An equation can be entered here to generate more complicated report outputs.\r \r \r   displaydesc\r   varchar(25)\r   NOT NULL \r   This field hold the textual desxcription of the field. The value entered here will be displayed in the header of reports but is only used for field setup in Reportbuilder for forms.\r \r \r   visible\r   0, 1 \r   1\r   Indicates whether the field will be displayed on the report or form.\r \r \r   columnbreak\r   0, 1 \r   1\r   Indicates whether the field will cause a column break after being displayed. If not set, the next field to display will be shown below this field. Column widths will default to the largest column displayed of all fields in a given column \r \r \r   params\r   text\r   NULL\r   This is an encoded (serialized) string of parameters used to further identify the field. Form fields contain significant information related to the font, color, position, etc. The field is freeform in that there are no criteria regarding the contents.'),(444,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/users_profiles.html','15.03.185','Table users_profiles','Table inventory_history\r \r \r \r Table users_profiles\r Table users_profiles contains the information to position the control panel features. The home page and each menu page can have their own control panel configuration by user. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   user_id\r   int(11)\r   0\r   Holds the user id for the control panel record. \r \r \r   page_id\r   varchar(32)\r   NULL\r   Holds the category (/modules) name of the record \r \r \r   module_id\r   varchar(32)\r   NULL\r   Holds the module (/category/pages/module) of the control panel record\r \r \r   column_id\r   int(3)\r   0\r   Holds the column number where the control panel entry is located \r \r \r   row_id\r   int(3)\r   0\r   Holds the row number where the control panel entry is located. \r \r \r   params\r   text\r   NULL\r   Holds encoded parameters which vary by module.\r \r \r \r &nbsp;'),(445,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/chart_of_accounts_history.html','15.03.35','Table chart_of_accounts_history','Table chart_of_accounts_history\r \r \r \r Table chart_of_accounts_history\r Table chart_of_accounts_history contains the historical and future\r balances of each general ledger account. Every journal entry affects\r this table. When an entry is posted to the ledger, the affected\r acocunts are incremented or decremented (according to accouting rules)\r to the posted period and rolled into future periods for as many periods\r have been created. This table is filled andmaintained by the system. DO\r NOT EDIT THE INFORMATION IN THIS TABLE or the books may become out of\r balance!\r \r NOTE: This table has the largest impact on a journal posting. Every\r posted entry rolls from the current period to the last period in the\r system. If too many fiscal years are generated in advance, the time to\r post an entry will significantly increase.\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Identifies the history record number.\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r periodint (11)0INDEX - The accounting period of the recordaccount_idchar (15)NOT NULLINDEX - Holds the general ledger account number (or id)beginning_balancereal (double)0Holds the beginning balance of the specific account for a given period.debit_amountreal (double) 0Holds the debit amount for the given ledger account for the given period.credit_amountreal (double)0Holds the credit amount for the given ledger account for the given period.budgetreal (double)0Holds the budgeted amount for the given ledger accout for the given period.last_updatedate0000-00-00Last update of the record.'),(446,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/countries.html','15.03.55','Table countries','Table countries\r \r \r \r Table countries\r Table countries \r \r Table Type: MyISAM\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r countries_id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto-increment number for record id.\r \r \r \r \r \r countries_name\r   varchar (64) NOT NULL\r   Name of the country. Can be modified for localization \r \r \r   countries_iso_code_2\r   char (2)\r   NOT NULL\r   ISO 2 Country Code (uppercase) \r \r \r   countries_iso_code_3\r   char (3) \r   NOT NULL\r   ISO 3 Country Code (uppercase)'),(447,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/accounting_periods.html','15.03.05','Table accouting_periods','Table accounting_periods\r \r \r \r \r Table accouting_periods\r Phreebooks uses accounting periods to track costs. 12 or 13 accounting\r periods make up a fiscal year. This table holds the acccounting period\r and the dates assigned to the period. It also maps the period to the\r fiscal year. Accounting periods may be changed only from the date of\r the last joiurnal entry to the end of the generated fiscal years. \r \r NOTE: It is best no to generate fiscal years beyond what is actually\r needed. PhreeBooks is a real-time posting accounting application and\r the balance sheet is updated fromthe posting date to the end of the\r fiscal year in the system. This will add additional sql accesses as the\r information may flow through the fiscal years.This\r table is first populated during install with the first fiscal year.\r Additional fiscal years can be added through the General Ledger -&gt;\r Utilities menu.Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r   \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r period\r int(11)\r 0\r (Primary Key) Holds the accounting period. Starting at 1 for the first peeriod of the fiscal year.\r \r fiscal_yearint(11)0Holds the fiscal year (2007, 2008, etc.)start_datedate0000-00-00Holds the calendar date of the start of the period (format YYYY-MM-DD)end_datedate0000-00-00Holds the calendar date of the end of the period (format YYY-MM-DD)date_addeddate0000-00-00Holds the date the period was first added (format YYYY-MM-DD)last_updatetimestampNOT NULLTimestamps the record if any changes are made to the record.'),(448,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/address_book.html','15.03.20','Table address_book','Table address_book\r \r \r \r Table address_book\r Table&nbsp;\r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r auto_increment\r N/A\r PRIMARY KEY - unique id assigned to each account entry\r \r \r \r \r CREATE TABLE address_book (&nbsp; address_id int(11) NOT NULL auto_increment,&nbsp; ref_id int(11) NOT NULL default \'0\',&nbsp; type char(2) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; primary_name varchar(32) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; contact varchar(32) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; address1 varchar(32) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; address2 varchar(32) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; city_town varchar(24) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; state_province varchar(24) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; postal_code varchar(10) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; country_code char(3) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; notes varchar(64) NOT NULL default \'\',&nbsp; PRIMARY KEY&nbsp; (address_id),&nbsp; KEY customer_id (ref_id,type)) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1 ;'),(449,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-DatabaseTables/inventory_assy_list.html','15.03.90','Table inventory_assy_list','Table inventory_assy_list\r \r \r \r Table inventory_assy_list\r Table inventory_assy_list hold the list of items used to assmeble an inventory item of type item assembly. \r \r Table Type: InnoDB\r \r \r \r \r Field\r Type\r Default\r Description\r \r \r id\r int (11)\r NOT NULL\r PRIMARY KEY - Auto increment field to hold unique ID \r \r \r   ref_id\r   int (11) \r   NOT NULL \r   Refers to the the id value in the inventory table of the item being assembled. \r \r \r   sku\r   varchar (15)\r   NOT NULL \r   Holds the sku of the inventory item that is part of the assembly refered to be ref_id \r \r \r   description\r   varchar (32) \r   NOT NULL \r   Holds the description of the sku. This may vary from the short name description pulled in be default in the bom tab in the maintain inventory script. \r \r \r   qty\r   float\r   0\r   Holds the quantity of the sku used in the assembly. The number need not be an integer.'),(450,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/03-Translations.html','15.3','Language Translations','Language Translations\r \r \r \r \r Language Translations\r This section discusses the programming guidelines for translatin PhreeBooks to languages other than English (US). The PhreeBooks website download section, www.PhreeBooks.com contains the language translations that have been generated to date. To start a new translation, it is best to download the translation that is most similar to your language, change the iso directory name, and edit the definitions as needed. \r The language files are broken into the following sections. \r \r   General Language - Loaded with all modules includes the menu defines, pull down menu defines, and general verbage used generically throughout the site.\r   Module Specific - Loaded with each module (and optionally with other modules if they are dependent on the module).\r   Service Modules/Control Panel Modules- Shipping, Payment, price sheets. These modules are designed to be added and removed to adapt to the varying needs of each user, locale, etc. \r   Installation - Language defines that are used only during the instllation routines.\r   Custom - User defined translations to overwrite the default language.\r   Help Files - The manual. Written in mostly HTML (ned to be directly translated).\r    Reports/Forms - Cofiguration headings for reports and forms. \r \r The first three sections are the key files to translate. The remaining four are recommended to translate but not required. You can install in english, read the manual in english and convert the reports your are interedted in but conversion would be preferred. The following list of files are part of the General and Module specific definitions. All the files need to be present for PhreeBooks to function properly. \r General Language File (replace the en_us with your appropriate iso code):\r \r     /modules/general/language/en_us/language.php\r \r Module Language Files:\r \r     /modules/accounts/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/banking/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/gen_ledger/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/hr/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/inventory/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/orders/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/quality/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/reportwriter/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/chart_of_accounts.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/countries.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/currency.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/departments.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/dept_types.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/inv_tabs.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/tax_auths.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/tax_rates.php\r   /modules/setup/language/en_us/modules/zones.php\r   /modules/services/import_export/language/en_us/language.php\r \r Control Panel Files:\r \r   /modules/general/language/en_us/boxes/personal_links.php\r   /modules/general/language/en_us/boxes/po_status.php\r   /modules/general/language/en_us/boxes/so_status.php\r   /modules/general/language/en_us/boxes/todays_sales.php\r \r Services (Payment), only needed if particular service module is loaded:\r \r    /modules/services/payment/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/services/payment/language/en_us/modules/cod.php\r   /modules/services/payment/language/en_us/modules/freecharger.php\r   /modules/services/payment/language/en_us/modules/moneyorder.php\r   /modules/services/payment/language/en_us/modules/nova_xml.php\r \r Services (Shipping), only needed if particular service module is loaded:\r \r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/modules/fedex.php\r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/modules/flat.php\r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/modules/freeshipper.php\r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/modules/item.php\r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/modules/storepickup.php\r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/modules/table.php\r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/modules/ups.php\r   /modules/services/shipping/language/en_us/modules/usps.php\r \r Services (Price Sheets):\r \r   /modules/services/pricesheets/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/services/pricesheets/language/en_us/modules/quantity.php\r \r Install (menu files):\r \r   /modules/install/language/en_us/language.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/about_phreebooks.html (Straight HTML translation) \r   /modules/install/language/en_us/admin_setup.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/chart_setup.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/coa_defaults.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/database_setup.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/finished.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/fiscal_setup.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/index.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/inspect.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/license.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/store_setup.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/system_setup.php\r \r Install (database setup files): \r \r   /modules/install/language/en_us/chart_of_accounts_types_list.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/config_data.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/countries_list.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/currencies_list.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/import_export_list.php\r   /modules/install/language/en_us/state_province_list.php\r \r Reports and Forms:\r Translated reports and forms are manged through the phreebooks website. The goal is to develop reports and then translate them for others to download. The reports may then be customized for each users application.\r Help File:\r What can I say, I wrote it in english, basic html with coding for the PhreeHelp popup help system. Needs complete re-write to convet to other languages.'),(451,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch15-ProgrammersRef/TechRefHome.html','15','Technical Reference','Technical Reference     Technical Reference This section discusses the programming guidelines, technical structure, database tables and programmers reference information.'),(452,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch20-Glossary/GlossaryHome.html','20','Glossary','Glossary     Glossary &nbsp;'),(453,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch16-TestSpec/TestSpecMain.html','16','Test Specification - Outline','Test Specification - Outline       BACKGROUND   INTRODUCTION   ASSUMPTIONS   TEST ITEMS     List each of the items (programs) to be tested.   FEATURES TO BE TESTED     List each of the features (functions or requirements) which will be tested or demonstrated by the test.   FEATURES NOT TO BE TESTED     Explicitly lists each feature, function, or requirement which won\'t be tested and why not.   APPROACH     Describe the data flows and test philosophy.     Simulation or Live execution, Etc.   ITEM PASS/FAIL CRITERIA Blanket statement     Itemized list of expected output and tolerances   SUSPENSION/RESUMPTION CRITERIA     Must the test run from start to completion?     Under what circumstances may it be resumed in the middle?     Establish check-points in long tests.   TEST DELIVERABLES     What, besides software, will be delivered?     Test report     Test software   TESTING TASKS Functional tasks (e.g., equipment set up)     Administrative tasks   ENVIRONMENTAL NEEDS     Security clearance     Office space &amp; equipment     Hardware/software requirements   RESPONSIBILITIES     Who does the tasks in Section 10?     What does the user do?   STAFFING &amp; TRAINING   SCHEDULE   RESOURCES   RISKS &amp; CONTINGENCIES   APPROVALS   &nbsp; &nbsp; Test Specification Items Each test specification should contain the following items: Case No.: The test case number should be a three digit identifer of the following form: c.s.t, where: c- is the chapter number, s- is the section number, and t- is the test case number. Title: is the title of the test. ProgName: is the program name containing the test. Author: is the person who wrote the test specification. Date: is the date of the last revision to the test case.      Background: (Objectives, Assumptions, References, Success Criteria): Describes in words how to conduct the test.      Expected Error(s): Describes any errors expected      Reference(s): Lists reference documententation used to design the specification.      Data: (Tx Data, Predicted Rx Data): Describes the data flows between the Implementation Under Test (IUT) and the test engine. Script: (Pseudo Code for Coding Tests): Pseudo code (or real code) used to conduct the test.'),(454,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch16-TestSpec/03-Vendors/01-VendorsMaint.html','16.03.01','Test Specification - Vendor Maintenance','Test Specification - Vendor Maintenance\r \r \r \r PhreeBooks Test Specification\r Title: Vendor Creation/Deletion/Maintenance\r Test No. 3.1  \r ProgName: PhreeBooks\r Modules\r Tested: modules/accounts/accounts.php (vendor condition) \r   Author: D. Premo \r Date: 10/01/2006 \r Background: (Objectives, Assumptions, References, Success Criteria)\r \r   Test the vendor interface for initial data entry, editting, and deletion.\r       Test the vendor pop-up screen, search capabilities and sorting capabilities.\r \r Objectives: Test the vendor setup and maintenance functions. \r Assumptions: Clean Install preferred but not requierd \r Pre-requisite Tests: Inventory Setup (to generate a purchase order) \r Reference Documents: Help - Vendor Maintenance\r   Test Procedure:\r \r   \r     Purpose of test \r     Expected Results \r     Notes\r   \r   \r     Accessing Vendor Entry Form \r     \r     \r     Maintain vendors form main pull down menu.\r     Enter new Vendor from main pull down menu.\r     Vendors can be added from either the maintain screen or the New Vendor drop-down \r   \r   \r     Create New Vendor\r     \r     Vendor ID is required\r       Vendor ID\'s cannot be duplicates.\r     Required fields are determined by the Setup - Vendors screen \r   \r   \r     Delete Vendor \r     Vendors can be deleted if no journal entries are in the system\r       Vendors cannot be deleted if a journal entry is present in the system \r     To test the no-delete error, a purchase order/purchase needs to be entered.\r   \r   \r     Edit Vendor \r     Vendor main record, shipping information and billing information as well as defaults can all be changed. \r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     Create Duplicate Vendor ID \r     Denied by the system.\r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     Add Billing Address \r     Required fields must be present or error \r     Required fields are the same as for the main address. \r   \r   \r     Delete Billing Address \r     Should be allowed at any time \r     Should test after a purchase order is generated to verify properly. \r   \r   \r     Add Shipping Address \r     Required fields must be present or error \r     Required fields are the same as for the main address. \r   \r   \r     Delete Shipping Address \r     Should be allowed at any time \r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     Change Account Terms \r     Terms updated in vendor record \r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     Address Errors (missing data, special characters, etc.) \r     Test for special characters (!, /, \\, \', &quot;, $, @, #, &amp;, *) \r     &nbsp;\r   \r   \r     Malicious Data Entry \r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r   \r \r &nbsp;'),(455,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/welcome.php','00','Welcome to PhreeBooks','Welcome to PhreeBooks     Welcome to PhreeBooks PhreeBooks is an open source accounting application designed for ease of use and robust functionality. Written in freely available PHP and MySQL, PhreeBooks has been tested on multiple platforms and browsers to ensure the broadest compatibility possible.  Some of the feature highlights are:     Web based interface   Full featured accounting engine   Complete inventory control including assemblies   Multiple company capablility    Multiple language capablility    Robust reporting capability    Full featured import/export capability   User friendly installation and setup script   Extensive user level security   PhreeBooks is release under the GNU license. &nbsp;'),(456,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch12-SoapXML/03-Customers/03-01-salesorders_import.html','12.03.01','Sales Order XML Definitions','Sales Order XML Definitions\r \r \r \r PhreeBooks Manual\r \r   \r     Previous Chapter \r     Chapter 1 - Sales Order Interface \r     Next Chapter \r   \r \r Chapter Heading\r Table of Contents\r 1.0 Introduction\r 2.0  Change History\r 3.0 Overview\r 4.0 General Programming Information\r 4.1 Access Request Interface Specification\r 4.2 Response Request Interface Specification\r 4.3 Examples\r 5.0 Programming Information\r 5.1 Access Request Interface Specification\r 5.2 Response Request Interface Specification\r 5.3 Examples\r 6.0 Appendices\r 6.1 Glossary\r 6.2 Return Status and Error Codes\r 6.3 Reference Tables\r 6.4 Frequently Asked Questions\r 1.0 Introduction\r This chapter covers the sales order interface. \r 2.0 Change History\r \r   \r     Revision\r     Description of Change \r     Date\r   \r   \r     1.0\r     Initial Release\r     1/1/2007\r   \r   \r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r   \r \r 3.0 Overview\r Sales orders are submitted to phreebooks through XML\r With the sales order interface you can:\r \r   Submit new sales orders  to the PhreeBooks system\r   Check status of existing sales orders\r   Change open sales orders\r   Close open sales orders\r \r 4.0 General Programming Information\r Access to the interface requires an open XML account in PhreeBooks, refer to user maintenance for information on creating and maintaining the XML users interface. \r Security \r DTD\'s \r SSL \r 4.1 Access Request Interface Specification\r *Yes - required if the container tag is present.\r \r   \r     Element (XMLPath) \r     Required/Cardinality\r     Type\r     Length\r     Description/Values\r   \r   \r     AccessRequest\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Access Request container tag \r   \r   \r     AccessRequest/\r     AccessUserID\r     Yes / One\r     Alpha-numeric\r     5 to 15\r     XML User ID  for request\r   \r   \r     AccessRequest/\r       AccessPassword\r     \r     Yes / One \r     Any\r     5 to 20\r     XML User Password for request \r   \r   \r     AccessRequest/\r     AccessFunction\r     Yes / One \r     Text\r     5 to 20\r     Must be \'SalesOrderEntry\' for this entry. This value matched with the username and password to verify access privileges to this function.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Top level container tag for the request \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r       Request\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container tag for the general parameters of the request\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     Request/\r     Version\r     \r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     4\r     The  XML interface version to the SalesOrder function. Current versions supported are:\r       1.00 - Intial release\r     \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     Request/\r     RequestAction\r     Yes / One \r     Text\r     15\r     The action requested for this transaction.\r          Possible options are:\r       New - New Sales Order\r       Status - Status an existing sales order\r       Change - Change an existing sales order\r       Close - Close an existing sales order\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r Request/ \r ReferenceName\r \r     No / Zero or One \r     Any\r     0 to 64\r     This field may be used to correlate the requests with the response for multiple submissions. The data from this field are returned with the response without modification. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r Request/ \r Originator\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container tag for originator of sales order \r     \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r Request/Originator/\r StoreID\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 16 \r     Contains the Store ID for the sales order submission. The value must correspond to a valid store ID as defined in the XML input/output configuration in PhreeBooks. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r Request/Originator/\r SalesRepID\r     No / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15 \r     Contains the Sales Rep ID for the sales order submission. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for a single sales order. \r         NOTE: At this time only one sales order can be processed per  XML transaction. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for the order summary information.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r SalesOrderID\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 16 \r     Sales Order ID reference. This value will be the key for processing and all future references to this sales order. This number must be unique to all values from all stores within the sales order journal. If left blank or omitted, a sales order number will be generated by the receiver. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r SalesOrderDate\r     No / Zero or One \r     Date Format \r     10 or 19\r     Date format must be of the form \'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS\' or abbreviated \'YYYY-MM-DD\'\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ItemTotal\r     No / Zero or One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Subtotal for all items contained within the sales order. This value will be verified against the quantities and prices of the sales orders line items. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r TaxTotal\r     No / Zero or One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Total tax charged for this sales order. This value will be verified against the total taxes charged within the sales orders line items. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ShippingTotal \r     No / Zero or One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Total shipping charged for this sales order.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ShippingCarrier\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     3 to 15 \r     Carrier to be used for this order. Must match an existing carrier as defined in PhreeBooks. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ShippingMethod\r     Yes / One\r     Alpha-numeric\r     3 to 15 \r     Shipping delivery service requested for this order. Must match codes as defined in PhreeBooks. Current codes are:\r     01 - Next Day Air\r       02 - Second Day Air\r       03 - Three Day Delivery\r       GD - Ground or Standard\r     \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/ \r OrderNotes\r \r     No / One \r     Text\r     0 to 255 \r     Customer or Requestor special notes associated with this order. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/ \r OrderSummary/\r Customer\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for the billing or customer information.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/Customer/\r CustomerID\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer ID link to requesting store.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/Customer/\r PrimaryName\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer or company name.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     Contact\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer   contact, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Telephone1\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer telephone number 1.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Telephone2\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer telephone number 2, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Fax\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer fax number, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Email\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Website\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer website, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     Address1\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 1.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     Address2\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 2.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     CityTown\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer city or town.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     StateProvince\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer state, province or region.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     PostalCode\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15\r     Customer zipcode or postalcode.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     CountryCode\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     2\r     Customer 2 character ISO country code. If no country code is provided, the country code found in Company/My Company will be used. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/SalesGLAccount\r     No / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     0 to 15 \r     Sales/Income GL Account for this sales order. If left blank, the order of precedence will be:\r     1. The customer default account from the customer record, if defined.\r     2. The default account as defined in My Company.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     TaxIDNumber\r     No / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     0 to 15 \r     Customer sales tax ID number. May also be used for resale number, FEIN, VAT license, etc.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/AccountNumber\r     No / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     0 to 15 \r     Customer account number.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo\r     No / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for the billing or customer information. If this container is not provided, the customer information will be used as the bill to information. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     PrimaryName\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer or company name.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     Contact\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer contact, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     Address1\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 1.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     Address2\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 2.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     CityTown\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer city or town.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     StateProvince\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer state, province or region.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     PostalCode\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15\r     Customer zipcode or postalcode.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     CountryCode\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     2\r     Customer ISO country code. If no country code is provided, the country code found in Company/My Company will be used. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo\r     No / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for the shipping information. If this container is not provided, the customer information will be used as the ship to information.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     PrimaryName\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer or company name.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     Contact\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer contact, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     Address1\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 1.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     Address2\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 2.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     CityTown\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer city or town.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     StateProvince\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer state, province or region.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     PostalCode\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15\r     Customer zipcode or postalcode.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     CountryCode\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     2\r     Customer ISO country code. If no country code is provided, the country code found in Company/My Company will be used. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ShipTo/ \r DropShipIndicator\r \r     No / Zero or One \r     Empty\r     0\r     Flag indicating this order is to be drop shipped. True if this container is present, false otherwise. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     BlindShipIndicator \r     No / Zero or One \r     Empty\r     0\r     Flag indicating this order is to be blind shipped. True if this container is present, false otherwise. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r ItemDetails\r     Yes / One to Many \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container tag for each line item in the sales order. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r ItemDetails/\r ItemID\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15\r     SKU/UPC code for the line item.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     ItemDetails/\r     Description\r     No / Zero to One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 64 \r     Short description of the line item.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     ItemDetails/\r     Quantity\r     Yes / One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Quantity of the line item being ordered.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     ItemDetails/\r     UnitPrice\r     Yes / One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Unit price  of the line item being ordered.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     ItemDetails/\r     SalesTax\r     No / Zero to One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Sales tax  of the line item being ordered. This field must match one of the sales tax rates define in PhreeBooks to properly alloate the tax to the proper tax authorities.\r   \r \r &nbsp;\r 4.2 Response Request Interface Specification\r *Yes - will be present if the container tag is present.\r \r   \r     Element (XMLPath) \r     Required/Cardinality\r     Type\r     Length\r     Description/Values\r   \r   \r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r   \r \r &nbsp;\r 4.3 Examples\r 5.0 Programming Information\r 5.1 Access Request Interface Specification\r 5.2 Response Request Interface Specification\r 5.3 Examples\r 6.0 Appendices\r 6.1 Glossary\r 6.2 Return Status and Error Codes\r 6.3 Reference Tables\r 6.4 Frequently Asked Questions\r &nbsp;'),(457,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch12-SoapXML/03-Customers/03-XMLCustomerHome.html','12.03','SOAP/XML Receivables Interface','SOAP/XML Receivables Interface\r \r \r \r \r SOAP/XML Receivables Interface\r PhreeBooks has an SOAP/XML interface build in to support XML type transfers that allow data to be inserted into and generated from the system. This will allow interfaces to third party applications and data transfers. Current XML definitions exist for:\r Sales Orders\r Submit Sales Orders (Import)\r Sales Invoices \r &nbsp;\r Future Definitions\r Generate Sales Order\r Cancel Sales Order\r Status Sales Order\r Invoice Sales Order\r Update Sales Order\r Submit Sales Invoice\r   Update Sales Invoice\r   Ship Sales Invoice\r   Status Sales Invoice'),(458,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch12-SoapXML/XMLHome.html','12','SOAP/XML Interface','SOAP/XML Interface     SOAP/XML Interface PhreeBooks has an SOAP/XML interface build in to support XML type transfers that allow data to be inserted into and generated from the system. This will allow interfaces to third party applications and data transfers. Current XML definitions exist for: Receivables Sales Orders (Import) Payables &nbsp; Inventory   Inventory (Export)'),(459,'http://localhost/phreebooks2/doc/manual/ch01-Introduction/04-02-Rev1p4.html','01.04.07','PhreeBooks Release 1.4','PhreeBooks Release 1.4\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r PhreeBooks Release 1.4\r // 2007-12-04 Change log, release 1.3.1 to Release 1.4\r   /doc/manual/ch01-Introduction/04-02-Rev1p4.html (this file) \r /doc/manual/ch01-Introduction/04-RevHistory.html\r /doc/manual/version.txt\r   /includes/version.php\r /modules/install/updater.php\r /modules/install/updates/R131toR14.php\r // *************************** sql statements ***************************//\r // sql statements are rolled into the base release and incorporated into the updater script for automatic db update\r // *************************** code changes ***************************//\r // 2008-01-21 - Misc Bug fixes \r /modules/banking/functions/banking.php ( clean up code/balance not calculated correctly ) \r /modules/banking/pages/bills/pre_process.php\r /mod